column5: Water very clear,but not much action lately. Slow for most. I guess the water still needs to get colder.Going to try again this Saturday,but noticed very few people out last Saturday on a very nice day. What do you guys think?. Is it the calm before the storm?. Any ideas,or comments?. Thanks davey.For someone who pm'd to my post,no specifics were given,either help or not!
I don't think you're fishing high enough in the system.
Up coming rains will change all that Davey. Did ya down size that float?
Yes I went to a 5 gr float,but you could see clearly. Sorry guys for the precise areas that I posted. My bad.
The first rule of fight club is not to talk about fight club  Good advice already given, you'll wanna fish higher up in the system bud.
Where would the UFC be if they didnt talk.LMAO
Yup all the fish are hiding out in the C&R zone don't bother with any other parts of that river....

I was there Sunday and went 0/0 saw a couple of fish being caught, the high lite of my day was wading across said river and not falling in!  And yes lets keep the river that everybody knows about a secret!!!
Thanks guys for your input,I will hope for rain or head to higher waters:worthy:
